To address the accessibility issue concerning the contrast ratio according to WCAG 2.1, AAA standards, adjustments to the CSS styles for better color contrast between the foreground and background colors are needed. The WCAG 2.1 AAA requirements mandate a contrast ratio of at least 7:1 for normal text and 4.5:1 for large text. 

Based on your provided source code, below are revised styles with enhanced contrast ratios to meet the stricter WCAG 2.1 AAA criteria:

```css
.pl20 {
    color: #000000; /* Changed to black for higher contrast */
    background-color: #ffffff;
}

.lastpl20 {
    color: #000066; /* Darker blue for better contrast */
    background-color: #ffffff;
}

.is-exclusive {
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #b30000; /* Darker red for better visibility */
}

.tag-new {
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #990000; /* Adjusted for better contrast ratio */
}

.is-breaking-news {
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #b30000; /* Consistent with .is-exclusive for better contrast */
}

.wocc {
    color: #ffd700; /* Using gold color for contrast */
    background-color: #4b0082; /* Indigo for accessibility */
}

.is-paywalled {
    color: #000000; /* Changed to black */
    background-color: #e6b3e6; /* Lighter purple for adequate contrast */
}

/* For .is-exclusive and .is-paywalled, since the styles were repeated, the last instance is considered. Adjusted to ensure both legibility and design consistency. */

.button_cVc76primary_vX6Hsfull-width_Orq_econsent_BHP9G {
    color: #000000; /* Black for readability */
    background-color: #c2c2c2; /* Light grey for contrast */
}
```

In the adjustments above, color contrasts were improved to ensure at least a 7:1 ratio for text against its background, aiming for AAA compliance. Darker shades of red and blue are used for critical elements such as `.is-exclusive` and `.lastpl20` to ensure readability. For elements such as `.wocc`, contrasting colors like gold on indigo provide both aesthetics and accessibility. Always remember to test actual contrast ratios using dedicated tools like the WebAIM Contrast Checker, as the precise visual perception may vary depending on the exact hues and context.

